<br>
I have only been up to level 47 on other server with a wizard but from all acounts the game chages once you hit 50+, and this is true with most classes.  roles change over time.  What you might do now with your class you may not like doing latter.  All depends on your preferance, so I'd recomend researching it a little.<br>
<br>
Also don't be affraid to take critisism no matter how badly worded somene makes it.  Sometimes someone who's been playing awile may ask you to stop doing somthing or start doing something different, and they may word there request to sound offencive.  <br>
<br>
However take the initiative and be polite back and ask the veteran <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WHY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  There are many little tricks those who have played a class may know, things about agro controll and pulling and casting and pretty much everything.  If someone asks you to stop doing something or start doing something either (A) they don't know what they are talking about, or (B) they do know what they are talking about and you have an oportunity to learn something new about grouping your class and other classes that will help you.  Don't be afraid to ask why, if you don't know the why then it can come accross as an order.  So find out the why behind someones request if they make one.<br>
<br>
Also all you vetrans, if you need to corect or guide a newbee to do something different send them a tell so as not to bring it out in the open in front of everyone that they were doing something wrong becase that method can end up being demoralizing.  Instead keep it private and it will be better for bolth of you.  <br>
<br>
One other thing to those that are new.  Many on this server have played MANY classes up to high levels, so even though you may be playing a wizard and some cleric is starting to act like they know everything about your class don't be supprised if they actualy do.  They may have a 60 level wizard on anouther server, or a 60th level bard, or cleric or anything or even a combination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator<br>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 4:36:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1107.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bestest tip ..</span><hr size=1> absolutely positively without question, reservation or anything else I can say, the number one tip that I would give the struggling newbie is:<br>
