<br>
Second line can ( but doesn't need to be, some people hate additional spam,) say &quot;/g Assisting %t&quot; or some variant thereof.<br>
<br>
Find out who your main tank is, ask who it is right as you are invited to the group, and change your assist key accordingly.  Use that assist button.  Don't just randomly whack on whatever critter is closest to you or ugliest, or whatever.  Enchanters/bards/people who are to root mobs will thank you for it.  <br>
<br>
Also, the /consider system is pretty goofy.  If you are soloing your new character, and the bat, gnoll, and spiderling all /con blue to you, don't assume that each is as easy to kill as the other.  That bat is probably the weakest, in this example.  That gnoll may have a weapon, and hit you pretty hard.  That spider may be able to poison you, and you might get killed by it.  In other areas, you may be hunting wolves and bears, and get killed by some random NPC who hits like Mike Tyson.<br>
<br>
If this is your first character, and you chose this server to do it on, you are in very good hands.  If you are polite and open to advice/criticism (and listen to it,) you should do well.  Yes, you will run into those that are not good people, but I find that for the most part people are very honorable here.<br>
<br>
<br>
Edit:  I edited it myself.  Rude of me.<br>
