<br>
Most newbie zones are pretty good (Toxx being a big exception). The second worst newbie zone (IMHO) is freeport. Its seems nice, but this an illusion. Even for newbie creatures, the MoBs are poor. If you weren't born in Freeport, don't go there in your early levels. If you were, head to North Ro or East commons as soon as you're strong enough to do so (NRo at about lvl 2 or 3, the east commons about level 3 or 4). I can't image leaving butcherblock for freeport's newbie area.<br>
<br>
Your faction is best in your starting city which means you can buy food/spells a little cheaper and do more quests.<br>
